{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "devops-sandbox-stage5",
    "name": "DevOpsSandbox-Stage5",
    "description": "Test pack for HNG14 DevOps Stage 5 — DevOps Sandbox Platform.\n\nFolders are ordered as a single linear flow. Run with the Collection Runner top-to-bottom against either the Local or Server environment.\n\n## Variable chaining\n\n- `Lifecycle > Create env` writes `created_env_id`, `created_env_name`, `created_env_url` to the environment.\n- All later requests use those.\n- `Cleanup > Destroy env` clears them.\n\n## What this pack proves\n\nAcceptance rows (see `governance/03_ACCEPTANCE_CRITERIA.md`):\n  - A28-A35 (Control API endpoints)\n  - A36-A40 (error contract)\n  - A18-A21 (outage simulation)\n  - A22-A24 (health monitoring observable through API)\n  - B17-B25 (implied: idempotency, error shape, ID format)\n\n## Auth\n\nIf `apiToken` is set, every request sends `X-API-Token: {{apiToken}}`. If empty, requests go unauthenticated — matches the platform default.\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "apikey",
    "apikey": [
      { "key": "key",   "value": "X-API-Token",   "type": "string" },
      { "key": "value", "value": "{{apiToken}}",  "type": "string" },
      { "key": "in",    "value": "header",        "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Skip auth header when token is unset — the platform runs open by default.",
          "if (!pm.environment.get('apiToken')) {",
          "    pm.request.headers.remove('X-API-Token');",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Global checks every response should pass.",
          "pm.test('Content-Type is JSON when body is non-empty', function () {",
          "    if (pm.response.text() && pm.response.text().length > 0) {",
          "        pm.expect(pm.response.headers.get('Content-Type') || '').to.match(/application\\/json/);",
          "    }",
          "});",
          "pm.test('Response time < 5s', function () {",
          "    pm.expect(pm.response.responseTime).to.be.below(5000);",
          "});"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0. Pre-flight",
      "description": "Cheap sanity checks before the lifecycle flow.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List envs (baseline)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs"]
            },
            "description": "Should succeed even if no envs exist. Records the starting count so the cleanup folder can verify we netted zero new envs at the end."
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Body has envs array', () => pm.expect(body).to.have.property('envs').that.is.an('array'));",
                  "pm.environment.set('baseline_env_count', body.envs.length);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "1. Lifecycle — happy path",
      "description": "Create → list → logs → health → outage crash → outage recover → destroy.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create env",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"{{demo_env_name}}\",\n    \"ttl_minutes\": {{demo_env_ttl_minutes}}\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('201 Created', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has env_id matching env-[0-9a-f]{8}', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body.id).to.match(/^env-[0-9a-f]{8}$/);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Has name, ttl_minutes, status, url, expires_at', () => {",
                  "    ['name','ttl_minutes','status','url','expires_at','created_at'].forEach(k => {",
                  "        pm.expect(body, `missing ${k}`).to.have.property(k);",
                  "    });",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Status is one of creating|running', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(['creating','running']).to.include(body.status);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.environment.set('created_env_id',   body.id);",
                  "pm.environment.set('created_env_name', body.name);",
                  "pm.environment.set('created_env_url',  body.url);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Wait 6s for container readiness",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "// Cheap sleep — gives the app container time to bind its port",
                  "// and the monitor time to take its first poll.",
                  "setTimeout(() => {}, 6000);",
                  "const start = Date.now();",
                  "while (Date.now() - start < 6000) { /* spin */ }"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List envs (created one is present)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "const id = pm.environment.get('created_env_id');",
                  "pm.test('Created env appears in list', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body.envs.map(e => e.id)).to.include(id);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Each env has ttl_remaining_seconds', () => {",
                  "    body.envs.forEach(e => pm.expect(e).to.have.property('ttl_remaining_seconds'));",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get logs",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs/{{created_env_id}}/logs",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs", "{{created_env_id}}", "logs"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has lines array <= 100', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('lines').that.is.an('array');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.lines.length).to.be.at.most(100);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Get health (last 10)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs/{{created_env_id}}/health",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs", "{{created_env_id}}", "health"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Has checks array <= 10', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('checks').that.is.an('array');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.checks.length).to.be.at.most(10);",
                  "});",
                  "if (body.checks.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.test('Check has timestamp, http_status, latency_ms', () => {",
                  "        ['timestamp','http_status','latency_ms'].forEach(k => {",
                  "            pm.expect(body.checks[0], `missing ${k}`).to.have.property(k);",
                  "        });",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Trigger outage — crash",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n    \"mode\": \"crash\"\n}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs/{{created_env_id}}/outage",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs", "{{created_env_id}}", "outage"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('202 Accepted', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Echoes mode=crash', () => pm.expect(body.mode).to.eql('crash'));",
                  "pm.test('Returns env_id', () => pm.expect(body.env_id).to.eql(pm.environment.get('created_env_id')));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Trigger outage — recover",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n    \"mode\": \"recover\"\n}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs/{{created_env_id}}/outage",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs", "{{created_env_id}}", "outage"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('202 Accepted', () => pm.response.to.have.status(202));",
                  "pm.test('Echoes mode=recover', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().mode).to.eql('recover'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Error paths",
      "description": "Negative tests — every error path returns the unified error shape.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get logs for non-existent env (404)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs/env-deadbeef/logs",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs", "env-deadbeef", "logs"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('404 Not Found', () => pm.response.to.have.status(404));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Error shape: error.code = not_found', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body).to.have.property('error');",
                  "    pm.expect(body.error.code).to.eql('not_found');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Create env with invalid name (400)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n    \"name\": \"---NOPE---\",\n    \"ttl_minutes\": 5\n}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('422 Unprocessable Entity', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('Error code = validation_error', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body.error.code).to.eql('validation_error');",
                  "});",
                  "pm.test('Error has details array', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body.error).to.have.property('details').that.is.an('array');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Outage with invalid mode (422)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n    \"mode\": \"vaporize\"\n}" },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs/{{created_env_id}}/outage",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs", "{{created_env_id}}", "outage"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('422 Unprocessable Entity', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));",
                  "pm.test('Error code = validation_error', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().error.code).to.eql('validation_error');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "3. Cleanup",
      "description": "Destroy the env created in folder 1, then verify the platform returned to baseline.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Destroy env",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs/{{created_env_id}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs", "{{created_env_id}}"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('204 No Content or 200 OK', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect([200, 204]).to.include(pm.response.code);",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Destroy same env again (idempotent — 404)",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs/{{created_env_id}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs", "{{created_env_id}}"]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('404 on second delete', () => pm.response.to.have.status(404));",
                  "pm.test('Error code = not_found', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(pm.response.json().error.code).to.eql('not_found');",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Final list (back to baseline)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v{{apiVersion}}/envs", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["api", "v{{apiVersion}}", "envs"] }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "const baseline = parseInt(pm.environment.get('baseline_env_count') || '0', 10);",
                  "pm.test('Net zero new envs vs baseline', () => {",
                  "    pm.expect(body.envs.length).to.eql(baseline);",
                  "});",
                  "pm.environment.unset('created_env_id');",
                  "pm.environment.unset('created_env_name');",
                  "pm.environment.unset('created_env_url');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
